Hi Mike,

How big is the seed list? I believe, but I am not sure, that during the 
recovery the seeds would be re-scheduled if you use the original seeds 
list. It would be easy to check by exploring the current recover log. 
Another reason for the larger queued list can be due the newly scheduled 
prerequisites like dns and robots.txt URIs. However, I would think that 
would not cause the queued list to triple in size.

In general, when recovering the crawl from the recover log, I have been 
using the empty seeds list. When the seeds list is used for scoping, I 
would create a separate scope file to mimic wanted scope.

I hope this helps.
